I used WhatWeb to perform technology fingerprinting on the target website. The tool identified technologies such as jQuery, HTTP headers, cookies, and security configurations. This helps understand the technology stack and identify potential vulnerabilities related to outdated libraries or misconfigured headers.

WhatWeb Command Used
whatweb -v -a 3 https://hackthissite.org
Explanation:
whatweb
Website fingerprinting tool used to detect technologies like CMS, frameworks, server type, and libraries used by a website.
-v
Verbose mode.
Shows detailed output like detected plugins, headers, and technology information.
-a 3
Aggression level.
Controls how deeply WhatWeb scans the target.
Levels:
-a 1 → Passive scan
-a 2 → Moderate scan
-a 3 → Aggressive scan (commonly used)
-a 4 → Very aggressive scan

https://hackthissite.org
Target website being scanned.

Most Useful Commands:

Scan a single website
whatweb https://example.com

Scan with aggressive detection
whatweb -a 3 https://example.com

Scan multiple targets from file
whatweb -i targets.txt

Save results to file
whatweb -i targets.txt --log-brief results.txt

Detailed output report
whatweb -i targets.txt --log-verbose detailed.txt






1️⃣ WHOIS

Purpose:
WHOIS is used to find information about a domain such as:
• Domain owner
• Registrar
• IP ranges
• Name servers
• Registration dates

Command:
whois hackthissite.org

What it tells you:
• Organization owning the domain
• Name servers (DNS servers)
• IP blocks sometimes belonging to the company
• Contact information

Why pentesters use it:
Helps identify infrastructure owned by the organization and sometimes reveals additional domains.

--------------------------------------------------

2️⃣ NSLOOKUP

Purpose:
NSLookup is used to query DNS records of a domain.

Basic Command:
nslookup hackthissite.org

Output shows:
• Domain IP address
• DNS server used to resolve the query

--------------------------------------------------

Common DNS Records to Query

Check A Record (IP address)
nslookup hackthissite.org

Check Name Servers
nslookup -type=ns hackthissite.org

Check Mail Servers
nslookup -type=mx hackthissite.org

Check TXT Records (sometimes contain secrets)
nslookup -type=txt hackthissite.org

--------------------------------------------------

Example Workflow in Recon

1. Find domain info
whois hackthissite.org

2. Find domain IP
nslookup hackthissite.org

3. Find name servers
nslookup -type=ns hackthissite.org

4. Find mail servers
nslookup -type=mx hackthissite.org

--------------------------------------------------

Why this is important in bug bounty

• Reveals infrastructure
• Shows DNS configuration
• Helps find additional attack surface
• Sometimes exposes internal services






DNS reconnaissance is important because it reveals the target’s infrastructure, servers, email systems, and possible weak points before scanning or attacking.




